import time
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def PLA(train_data_loc, initW):
    ''' PLA algorithm
    Params: train_data_loc - the exact path of the dataset (.txt)
            initW - the initial value of W vector, usually [0,0,0]
    Returns: A array contains the latest W vector, processing time, iteration times means times that W vector changes
    '''
    #   start the timer 
    tic = time.time()
    #   read the data
    train_data = pd.read_table(train_data_loc,names =['X1','X2','label'],header =None,sep = ',')
    #   init W vector
    W = initW
    #   count the W update times   
    iteration_cnt = 0
    #   preprocess data: add X0 = 1 to each row
    train_data.insert(0,'X0',np.ones(np.shape(train_data)[0]))
    trainArray = train_data.values
    
    error_cnt = 1
    #   naive cycle
    #   if there is no bias/ nothing to update, the while loop will stop
    while error_cnt !=0:
        error_cnt = 0
        for i in range(len(trainArray)):
            x= trainArray[i][:3]
            y= trainArray[i][3]
            if np.sign(np.dot(W,x)) != y:
                W = W + y*x
                iteration_cnt +=1
                error_cnt+=1
    #  end the timer
    toc=time.time()
    elapsed_time = toc - tic

    #  plot part
    positive_points = train_data.loc[train_data['label'] == 1]
    negative_points = train_data.loc[train_data['label'] == -1]
    plt.scatter(positive_points.X1,positive_points.X2, c='none',marker = '.', edgecolors =['blue'],s=150)
    plt.scatter(negative_points.X1,negative_points.X2, c='r',marker = 'x')

    x1 = np.linspace(-100, 100)
    y1 = (-W[0]-W[1]*x1)/W[2]
    plt.plot(x1,y1,c='k',label='Learned line')
    plt.legend(loc =1)
    plt.xlabel('X$_1$')
    plt.ylabel('X$_2$')
    
    return [W, elapsed_time, iteration_cnt];

result = PLA('traindata_balanced_20.txt', [0,0,0])
print('Final W:',result[0], '\nElapsed time:', result[1])
